    en: "Every eligible New York resident has the right to vote. Since 2021, voting rights are restored immediately upon release from incarceration — no waiting period, no probation completion required. Registration is available online, by mail, at the DMV, and at the local Board of Elections; the registration deadline in NY is 10 days before Election Day, with an affidavit (provisional) ballot as a fallback at the polling place. Employers must give time off to vote. Understanding these rights prevents eligible voters from being turned away."
